$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Shell Folders

This registry should not be used. In fact, it contains the entry
*!Do not use this registry key* whose value is *Use the SHGetFolderPath* or *SHGetKnownFolderPath* function instead.
-
This is explained by → https://devblogs.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20110322-00/?p=11163[Raymond Chen] and
→ https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/technet-magazine/cc160778(v=msdn.10)[Technet].


